</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="117" pageNumber="395" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="117.[749,1341,1558,1985]" pageId="117" pageNumber="395">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="J. A. Allen" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[751,1009,1677,1710]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="117" pageNumber="395" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="difficilis">Peromyscus difficilis</taxonomicName>
is in the true: species group. Its taxonomy was revised in 1961 and 1976. More recent biochemical, karyotypic, and DNA sequence data indicate that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ord" authorityYear="1818" box="[815,902,1843,1868]" class="Mammalia" family="Sciuridae" genus="Sciurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="117" pageNumber="395" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="griseus">griseus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="J. A. Allen" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[922,1022,1843,1868]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="117" pageNumber="395" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nasutus">nasutus</taxonomicName>
, and penicillatus forms should be assigned to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="J. A. Allen" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[1068,1203,1874,1907]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="117" pageNumber="395" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nasutus">P. nasutus</taxonomicName>
. Five subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
